    "index": 1,
    "id": "df017b7a-9312-47dc-af89-1c2eaa97fe3d",
    "body": "I wanted to flag an issue I’ve noticed while creating an objective. Several times now, while I’m typing inside the creating a new objective/description area, if I move my mouse from right to left within that section, the chat disappears and takes me back to the main Objectives menu.\n\nWhen that happens, the draft I was working on is lost, and I have to go back into the objective and start typing everything again. This has happened multiple times, so I’m not sure if a swipe/back navigation behavior is being triggered by the mouse movement or if it’s a bug within the Objectives section.\n\nAlso, if possible, it may be helpful to have some type of draft or autosave option while writing messages or creating objectives, so the user doesn’t lose what they have already typed if the page refreshes, closes, or navigates away by accident.\n\nWould it be possible to take a look at this? Thank you!",
    "status": "fixed",
    "createdAt": "2026-05-29T21:05:45.250515+00:00",
