    "body": "Hey Andrew, I have another small feedback item/question.\n\nOn some web platforms, when navigating between sections, you can right-click a tab or button and open it in a new browser tab or window. For example, if I’m working in the Objectives section, it would be helpful to right-click and open Fix-It in a separate tab without having to duplicate the entire page first. Would it be possible to add that type of option to the OMP navigation, or is the best workaround simply to duplicate the browser tab and then navigate to the section needed? It may be a small item, but I think it could make it easier to work across multiple sections at the same time.",
